{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 15:10:30.023507", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nExecutive summary\n- The Clos fabric’s control plane (EBGP) and inter-router forwarding appear healthy.\n- The endpoint pc_0_0 is down/unreachable at L2/L3. This is the only observed failure and explains failed host-to-host connectivity to 10.0.0.2.\n- Impact is isolated to reachability of pc_0_0; other components (pc_0_1 and all routers) are operating normally.\n\nExpected behavior\n- Each leaf advertises its directly connected /24 via EBGP.\n- Spines peer with super-spine and leaves; super-spine peers with all spines.\n- Hosts should be able to reach each other across the fabric (e.g., pc_0_1: 10.0.1.2 ↔ pc_0_0: 10.0.0.2).\n\nTests performed and key observations\n1) Control-plane/BGP health\n- BGP summaries on all routers are up with expected peers:\n  - leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200): 4 neighbors up; receiving 7 prefixes from each.\n  - leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201): 4 neighbors up; receiving 7 prefixes from each.\n  - spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100): 6 neighbors up; receiving prefixes from leaves and super-spine.\n  - spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101): 6 neighbors up; receiving prefixes from leaves and super-spine.\n  - super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000): 8 neighbors up; receiving prefixes as expected.\n- RIB samples:\n  - spine_router_0_0 has BGP routes to 10.0.0.0/24 via leaf_router_0_0 and 10.0.1.0/24 via leaf_router_0_1. Multiple other /24s are present as well, indicating proper distribution.\n  - leaf_router_0_1 learns 10.0.0.0/24 via a spine and has 10.0.1.0/24 as directly connected.\n\n2) Data-plane checks\n- pc_0_1 host config:\n  - IP 10.0.1.2/24, default via 10.0.1.1 (leaf_router_0_1). It successfully pings its gateway (10.0.1.1), indicating a healthy local L2 and L3 path.\n- pc_0_1 to leaf_router_0_0 SVI:\n  - pc_0_1 can ping 10.0.0.1 (leaf_router_0_0 SVI) successfully, proving the fabric data plane between pods/leaves is working.\n- pc_0_1 to pc_0_0:\n  - pc_0_1 